product_name: LancomeTeint Idole Ultra Wear Care and Glow Foundation
summary: SummaryLanc么me Teint Id么le Ultra Wear Care and Glow Foundation is a 24-hour healthy glow liquid serum foundation with buildable medium coverage to hydrate and smooth skin for a natural glow finish.
details: DetailsFeaturesBuildable Medium CoverageNatural Glow Finish82% serum based formula for maximum hydrationSuitable for all skin types including sensitive skinAvailable in 30 transfer-resistant, long-lasting shades9/10 women said their skin tone looked more even**9/10 women said their overall skin felt improved**After 3 weeks of use, women reported visibly improved skin and evened skin tone over time****In a consumer study with 107 women after 3 weeks of useBenefits24 hour healthy glow finishKey IngredientsHyaluronic Acid: hydrates and plumps the skin.Mandelic Acid: smooths and refines the skin.Contains 30% rose balm extract.Item 2598637How To UseFor light coverage: Apply with fingers, a damp sponge, or a foundation brush for durable wear.For medium coverage and maximum results: Apply with a flat foundation brush or an airbrush foundation brush, and apply using a stippling motion for a flawless finish.IngredientsDimethicone, Water, Isododecane, Alcohol Denat., Trimethylsiloxysilicate, Propylene Glycol, Glycerin, PEG/PPG-18/18 Dimethicone, Silica, Synthetic Fluorphlogopite, Polysilicone-11, Rosa Gallica Flower Extract, Moringa Oleifera Seed Extract, Polymnia Sonchifolia Root Juice, Sorbitol, Mandelic Acid, PEG-10 Dimethicone, Alpha-Glucan Oligosaccharide, Sodium Chloride, Sodium Hyaluronate, Sodium Hydroxide, Silica Silylate, Cellulose Acetate Butyrate, Aluminum Hydroxide, Ammonium Polyacryloyldimethyl Taurate, Disodium Phosphate, Disodium Stearoyl Glutamate, Hydroxyethylpiperazine Ethane Sulfonic Acid, Caprylyl Glycol, Citric Acid, Lactobacillus, Maltodextrin, Polyphosphorylcholine Glycol Acrylate, Polyvinyl Alcohol, Butylene Glycol, Tocopherol, Phenoxyethanol, Fragrance, Linalool, Geraniol, Limonene, Citral, Citronellol, Benzyl Alcohol.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: For light coverage: Apply with fingers, a damp sponge, or a foundation brush for durable wear.For medium coverage and maximum results: Apply with a flat foundation brush or an airbrush foundation brush, and apply using a stippling motion for a flawless finish.

reviews.headline: Love Lacome products
reviews.comments: Great coverage.

reviews.headline: Wonderful on my dry, mature skin! Thank you!
reviews.comments:
So ive always tried to wear lancome teinte idole in matte. Alot of others can still wesr with thier dry skin; i however, cannot. When this first came out, i bought right away. I was certain it would not work because shade was a dark orangey neutral for the lightest neutral. 

I am a pale mature and dry skin woman. It did oxidize a bit BUT, it stayed the neutral amd then seemed to work with my skin and like, color corrected or something. I have no idea.  I just know that i love this, looks beautiful, stays on all day, tad bit of a glow, but not really. Its a perfect hint of something.

reviews.headline: Clerk recommendation was a wrong color
reviews.comments: I sought help from the clerk for a color match.  She matched me with the wrong color and I can't use it.I use Lancome so it wasn't the product's problem.

reviews.headline: Love this foundation
reviews.comments: This foundation feels very good on my skin and covers very well!

reviews.headline: Love this foundation but ulta shipped me an expired one
reviews.comments: I ordered this march 2025 and have been using it and frankly i always loved this foundation. One time it was in front of me and i noticed 2024, took me a minute to realize ive been using an expired foundation since march. I got one for my mom the same day and it expires in december 2025. Ulta should not ship products that expired or have less than a year. Really upset about it, but the foundation itself is fantastic

reviews.headline: I would totally recommend this product.
reviews.comments: Awesome product. I would definitely buy this again.

reviews.headline: Paid $50+ for makeup that was 1.5 yrs expired.
reviews.comments: I went into my local Ulta for a new shade in this foundation. I was matched up and so I purchased it. The next morning, after I had applied it, I noticed the expiration date on the bottle said "exp. 02/2024." I was highly upset and called customer service which they did absolutely nothing about it. Not even a discount/coupon for next purchase. I called the store and  explained the story and asked if they had some that was fresh. I was put on hold, and when the employee came back to the phone, she stated all the bottles were expired and they had to pull them. I ended up returning the product and went to Dillard's and purchased the same foundation that has an expiration date of 2027. No more Ulta purchases for me!

reviews.headline: Amazing for oily skin
reviews.comments: So i know skin tints are the current trend but as an oily girl they just never work for me. But i still wanted a lightweight matte foundation and this is it! It last all day easily without transfer and gets slightly dewy throughout the day without seperating. Ive tried more highend and drug store setting sprays with it and they all work the pretty similar witht this foundation. I got shade 405W for summer. I did try to shade match myself during the winter but 400W was way too light and the other shades werent matching my undertone. I do hope they improve their medium shade range soon because i wish i could wear this foundation year around! For reference my summer shades are usually 334 for maybelline fit me, 345 in fenty, and brule in born this way. My winter shades are usually 330 in fit me, 335 in fenty, and warm sand in born this way.

reviews.headline: I'd buy again and it has sunscreen I it.
reviews.comments: I haven't used Lancome in years. Now that I am probably 20 years older,  I wanted to go back in time to use what worked for me. I was very colorful after trying on 15 or more shades at the store by myself. I found the right one. It's amazing!!!

reviews.headline: Beautiful finish, looks great on mature skin
reviews.comments: I'm 45 with dry skin and rosacea. This foundation looks amazing on my skin! The finish is very natural, the color is perfect, and it's long wearing. I will absolutely repurchase.

reviews.headline: Beautiful. But...shade range needs help
reviews.comments: This has a gorgeous finish and goes on easily. However, the lightest shade (105W) is still too dark for fair skin and is straight up YELLOW. The 110C is still too dark but at least not yellow. Lancome should make the same shade range as the original Teint Idole foundation. I don't get it!  I recommend this foyndation, but only if yoy don't have very fair skin.

reviews.headline: Great foundation but allergic to the fragrance
reviews.comments:
The foundation lasts through my 12 hour shifts without breaking down like most foundations I've tried. There was also limited transfer when taking my mask on and off throughout the day. In addition, it provided very good coverage with one layer and smoothed out the look of my textured skin. However, this foundation did not have a dewy/glowy appearance on my combination skin as expected. The major downside of this foundation was it was highly fragranced and the formula caused me to break out pretty significantly. Also, I felt the color was slightly darker (by approximately one or two shades) than it was portrayed on the model. 

I really wanted to keep this foundation but it just was too harsh on my sensitive skin. For those of you without issues to heavy fragrances this foundation is a beautiful choice. However, consider going with a lighter shade for a closer match.

reviews.headline: I would not buy this again.
reviews.comments: I will be returning this item, I did not like the coverage.

reviews.headline: Your Skin But Better
reviews.comments: Perfect shade match! It blends well and has light coverage. Has good texture ans looks and feels like skin. I am obsessed with this! I immediately purchased a second bottle.

reviews.headline: Worth trying
reviews.comments: This was a new foundation for me, I got a good deal during the spring beauty sale. So far I like it but not sure if I'd pay full price but definitely worth trying.

reviews.headline: Natural perfection with coverage!
reviews.comments: Light but effective coverage. Blends well. Prohibits oil build even after wearing all day!  Smooth without showing fine lines. I am 51 and have some signs of aging - this definitely gives me the younger look.

reviews.headline: makes eye makeup bleed
reviews.comments: love the color and smell and feel,but can't wear it as it makes my eyes look like a raccoon within hours of wearing it. even with waterproof/smudge proof liner/mascara

reviews.headline: nice product, difficult match
reviews.comments: This product is very nice.  However, matching to my skin has been a challenge...it took three color match sessions and still not right.  I use it lightly to avoid a weird color look.  too bad because it is a really good product.

reviews.headline: Highly recommend this

reviews.comments: I just bought this ! I barely have used and its gone already!? For such an expensive product you would think it would last longer. Such a waste. And NO I do not use a ton when doing make up.

faceoff_positive.comments: I really like this foundation.  It has good coverage, it feels good on and it wears very well.  This is just what I was looking for.  I have used the Teint Idole Ultra Wear Matte 24 hr formula in the past and I really liked it, but I wanted to find a good foundation that was not Matte, but had coverage and this formula is perfect!  I have a lighter medium neutral skin tone, but wanted a little more color.  The colors are somewhat forgiving.  I went with shade 335W and it is working out great for me.  I wore it to Mardi Gras and I think my makeup looked just as good after 4 hrs in the humidity as it did when we left.
faceoff_positive.headline: Just found my perfect match!

faceoff_negative.comments:
Lancomes shade ranges are now laughable they're so bad now. I've tried 110C which is a hair too pale and an odd peach pink (that is artifical and doesnt represent any real life skin tone,) 115C (which isn't cool at all, but super gold,) 220C which is slightly too dark and also an odd artifical peach pink. No way the models are wearing those shades in the photos. 

I've tried mixing them in different combinations to no avail. One more combo to try before I give up completely. Regenerie shade line is also wrecked. 115c and 220C used to be beautiful and realistic cool tone beige colors which is what cool skin toned people look like. Now they've wrecked it too with the odd artifical peach pink. Never seen such odd foundation colors before. Literally is the identical color of the peach/flesh crayola crayon. 

Whoever created these shades clearly has no knowledge of cool/light skin tones. The foundation itself is good. Yes, it stinks like the others said, but the smell goes away and it doesn't settle into fine lines like traditional mattes and isn't heavy like a mask. Really wished they had shades for light skin, but I guess they no longer wish to have us as customers and changed their shade range accordingly.
